{"id":979242642,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"3 days, 8 hours","timestamp":1687691754,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"116 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/979242642/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Count Zero Request Servers","memory":"104 MB","code":"class Solution {\n\n    public int[] countServers(int n, int[][] logs, int x, int[] queries) {\n        int m = queries.length;\n        int[] counts = new int[n + 1], output = new int[m];\n        TreeMap<Integer, ArrayList<Integer>> map = new TreeMap<>();\n        Arrays.sort(logs, Comparator.comparingInt(log -> log[1]));\n        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {\n            map.putIfAbsent(queries[i], new ArrayList<>());\n            map.get(queries[i]).add(i);\n        }\n        int a = 0, b = 0, c = n;\n        for (Map.Entry<Integer, ArrayList<Integer>> entry : map.entrySet()) {\n            int t = entry.getKey();\n            while (a < logs.length && logs[a][1] <= t) {\n                int s = logs[a++][0];\n                if (counts[s]++ == 0) c--;\n            }\n            while (b < a && logs[b][1] < t - x) {\n                int s = logs[b++][0];\n                if (--counts[s] == 0) c++;\n            }\n            for (int i : entry.getValue()) output[i] = c;\n        }\n        return output;\n    }\n\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"count-zero-request-servers","has_notes":false}
